reviews.review_text: I ordered Cod with fries and tartar sauce tonight and it caused me around 25 dollars or so. To be honest it s a little bit expensive to me as a student, but the food and its taste is definitely worth the price. The fish is fresh and tartar sauce is delicious and flavorful I m so into it after the first taste.  I will probably pay Fish Cafe a second visit.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi thank you for your very kind words and for visiting us, next time you come in come and say hello, I ll make sure to give you a better deal

reviews.review_text: Was running errand in the area. We actually waited over 30 minutes for them to open, it was well worth it! We got 3pcs snapper fish&chips! Good portion! The batter was crispy, fish was moist, perfectly seasoned! It was soooooo good, really hit the spot! Tartar sauce was light and refreshing, not heavy at all. I craved this again 3-4 times that same day, I m still thinking about it today! We also got the scallop, grilled, over rice, with garlic butter! Scallop was also perfectly cooked! Sweet and juicy! I enjoyed dipping the scallop in the butter and adding tartar sauce to the rice for the perfect bite! Food was a little slow but we went right when they open so it was understandable. I appreciate that the chef take his time to prepare the food properly instead of rushing them out. Service was friendly and casual, very warm and welcoming! We enjoyed our conversation with them and our time there. This was also the first time we took our puppy to a restaurant, we were glad it was a pleasant experience. Their supplies came late that day and we couldn t order what we originally wanted, but we would definitely be back for other dishes. What we ended up ordering turn out great though, so no complain there! But next time we want to try cod fish& chips, grilled calamari, and clam chowder. :) We wish they have deep fried oysters too, I think it will be amazing!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much, please come and run some errands in our area so we can spoil you again soon

reviews.review_text: Local restaurant with world class food. Chef Marcus is personable and goes out of his way to make sure you are taken care of. The fish grilled or blackened is always delicious. However, the calamari appetizer will always remain my favorite.

reviews.review_text: Great neighborhood restaurant.  I like the blackened fish with lemon butter sauce on the side. The fries are worth the calories here. If you re craving fish and chips make sure you eat here. They offer take out here.  Parking meters on 41st Ave is usually very easy.

It was an incredible experience dining here. Food was great, we had fish n chips and caesar salad. Chef and both waitresses were so kind and welcoming. It was a lovely experience. I just moved to Vancouver and this restaurant has definitely become my goto place.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your kind words, welcome to Vancouver.

reviews.review_text: Fish Cafe was great! Im from Toronto and my cousin mentioned BC has great seafood, its fresh. We started with the grilled calamari with garlic butter which was a great combo. I had a Greek salad with 1pc fish and chips. He had the grilled salmon on rice. For dessert we tried their chocolate cake (they didnt have anymore carrot cake). Its understandable that some menu items wouldnt be available due to the freshness of the food so we didnt get a chance to try their crab cakes or clam chowder. I would highly recommend the fish and chips, the snapper was very light and battered perfectly. Overall Im happy we visited and I would definitely go back if I visit BC again :) Parking: You may find free street parking if youre willing to park around the corner. Otherwise there is paid parking right in front of the restaurant.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for coming in tonight, I really pleased you guys enjoyed yourselves, thank you for taking the time to leave your thoughts here.

reviews.review_text: I absolutely love this place. This is the type of place you see in movies where the small local fish restaurant has one chef and two waitresses who know the local patrons by name and their usual orders. My favorite dish on the menu is their fish burger. If you re a fan of blackened fish or focaccia bread this menu item is for you. I ve had both the salmon and red snapper options and I ve been impressed every time. The fish is always cooked to perfection and the focaccia bread *chef kiss* The fries are also always crispy and fresh which just competes the dish. Make sure to get some of their tarter sauce on side because it s the perfect blend of creamy and tart. I will note that the typical wait time for your food to be served feels a bit longer than most restaurants but when you re served amazing food, the wait time doesn t matter. Order a drink and enjoy the company around you.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: WOW thank you so much, yeah that extra bit of tartare sauce is so good.

reviews.review_text: I really like the ambiance of this small cafe- casual and no nonsense. My partner and I prefer places like this where there is a limited menu with all the dishes executed very well. Its also an added bonus to be able to choose how your fish will be prepared (grilled, blackened or fried), and of course the fish is fresh & prepared to perfection.

reviews.review_text: Definitely the best fish and chips that I had in town. Marcus is a great chef making the food amazing and the staff is so friendly. Definitely I would visit again.

reviews.review_text: I was driving around looking for something to eat and saw this place...I stopped in and was warmly greeted by the young lady serving tables. It was toward the end of the night, so the fish options were limited, but it worked to my favor. I ordered the steelhead with my seafood platter, which I would not usually go for. Well, it was amazing! Blackened with that garlic butter...just simply awesome. The grilled calamari, scallops, and prawns were equally fresh and delicious and those fries were among the best I have had. I would recommend the fries over the rice, only because they are so good! All in all, it was an amazing meal and I am glad I stumbled upon this place. I will be back next time I am in Vancouver...

reviews.review_text: The best seafood meal in Vancouver!!! Fish Cafe is owned by South African, Marcus Stiller. He has become a legend in Vancouver for the excellent food and great service at his restaurant in Kerrisdale. Plus, the only place I know of in the Lower Mainland where one gets delicious grilled calamari with no batter. Others had snapper, cod and steelhead and was the best they d had! Even his fries are first rate!! Be sure to stop by for awesome flavourful South African cooking and hospitality. Make sure to introduce yourself to Marcus.

reviews.review_text: The Fish Cafe serves the best cooked fish in Vancouver, bar none.  Always fresh; if its not available that day, it comes off the menu.  Weve been coming here on at least a weekly basis for years and the quality has never dipped once.  The fish soup is sublime, with large chunks of fish every time.  My mother loves their fish and chips using cod; the fish is always moist and the batter is crunchy and light.  Even the fries are amazing.  Its worth pointing out that the fish and chips is cheaper here than at the White Spot and clearly on a completely different level.  I love the grilled trout and its never overcooked or dry, despite being such a thin, delicate piece of fish.  Portion sizes are always generous.  This is a comfortable neighbourhood spot, with really friendly and professional service.  Thanks to Marcus, his family and the staff for always making us feel welcome and VERY well fed.

reviews.review_text: It is a nice cozy little restaurant in the heart of Kerrisdale that serves only seafood.  The chef will cook ones fish either grilled or blackened.  They offer two soups on their a la carte menu, namely a fish soup and a clam chowder. It was packed when I got there at seven.  The waitress has an excellent memory of the drink order of the restaurant most loyal customers.  The clam chowder was very good.  The swordfish was most enjoyable.  As for their wine selection, it is very limited.  In fact, if one wants serious cocktails, go to Barra 41 at Balsam and 41st Ave.

reviews.review_text: Its a bit of hole in the wall, and very busy during dinner. I highly recommend a reservation so you get a table. My usual order is a house salad to start, blackened steelhead with fries, and either the chocolate or carrot cake for dessert. Their desserts deserve special mention. I know theyre not made in house, but theyre probably my favorite cakes at the time of writing.
